End a Messaging Session

When youâ€™re done helping a customer, end the messaging session from the conversation window or from the Messaging Sessions list view.

Available in: Lightning Experience. This article applies to: Messaging for In-App and Web, standard and enhanced WhatsApp, standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger, standard and enhanced SMS, enhanced Apple Messages for Business, and Bring Your Own Channel

To end a messaging session:

From the conversation window in an active messaging session that you own, click End Chat.
In the list of messaging sessions, find the ones you want to end.
Click the action menu next to a messaging session and select End Session. If multiple sessions are selected, select End Sessions.

Keep these considerations in mind:

* If you go offline during an active messaging session, the session status changes depending on your business's capacity model.
* If you log out of Omni, ongoing sessions will end.
* If you close a session tab without ending the session, you're prompted to choose between ending the session and marking it inactive.
* Messaging sessions end automatically after 24 hours in standard channels or 48-54 hours in enhanced channels if the customer doesn't respond.

Required editions and user permissions:
Messaging for In-App and Web permission set license
Messaging for In-App and Web user permission
Owner of the messaging session

OR:

Messaging Agent
Owner of the messaging session
title: Ending a Messaging Session in Service Cloud
